author: David Simon
content: Albert Camus, a great humanist and existentialist voice, pointed out that
  to commit to a just cause with no hope of success is absurd. But then he also noted
  that not committing to a just cause is equally absurd. But only one choice offers
  the possibility for dignity. And dignity matters.
